narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: an understanding of communist and post-communist Polish film, women in cinema, and understanding of censorship in Polish film

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I think this being a class that few film students take, it's difficult to succeed writing papers in this course. If there was a paper writing workshop prior to the midterm and final paper, that would be very useful.
strengths- such interesting films, prof is really nice weaknesses- only one screening a week sometimes made it difficult to view the films
Professor Illakowicz is undoubtedly the greatest strength of this course. Her passion for the subject colors and enlivens every discussion. Amazing films taught by an amazing professor!

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! The films we watched were all so different and interesting.
Yes! This course is a must take!
